## SYSTEM UNDER REVIEW

This compliance framework is anchored to the following specific system. All analysis defaults to this context unless a different system is explicitly introduced.

- **System Name:** DRRS P-Level Calculator
- **Purpose:** Automates Personnel Readiness (P-Level) calculation per MCO 3000.13B paragraph 7c for USMC S/G-1 sections.
- **Platform:** Static client-side web application. No backend server, no database, no API endpoints.
- **Hosting:** GitHub Pages (static file hosting) or any static HTTP server. See ADR-1.
- **Data Processing Model:** All CSV parsing and calculation execute in the user's browser. No personnel data leaves the user's machine. No server logs, no database breach surface.
- **Persistence:** Browser `localStorage` stores only operator preferences (as-of date, unit policy toggle). No PII or CUI is persisted. A "Wipe Local Data" button clears all browser-side data.
- **Encryption:** Optional AES-256-GCM + PBKDF2-SHA256 encryption for exported unit profile JSON files (Web Crypto API).
- **Authentication:** None. The app has no user accounts, no login, no session management. Access control is inherited from the hosting environment (e.g., CAC-gated SharePoint, GitHub repo visibility).
- **Network Connection to DoD IS:** None. The app does not connect to NIPRNET, SIPRNET, MCEN, DRRS-MC, AAA, TFSMS, or any other DoD information system. Data enters only via manual CSV upload from the operator's workstation.
- **Architecture Decision Records:** ADR-1 (no server, ever, for this PoC), ADR-2 (DRRS export is paste-into-Remarks, no API), ADR-3 (Next.js uses `output: 'export'` for static build).

**Compliance Implications of This Architecture:**

The following controls from NIST SP 800-171r3 and other standards are **not applicable** to this system due to its static client-side architecture:

| Control Area | Status | Rationale |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Row Level Security / multi-tenant isolation | N/A | No database, no server, no multi-tenancy |
| Multi-Factor Authentication (03.05.02) | N/A | No authentication system; access control is at the hosting layer |
| Session management / replay-resistant auth (03.05.03) | N/A | No sessions; stateless static page |
| Credential storage (hashing, salting) | N/A | No credentials stored |
| TLS 1.2+ for data in transit (03.13.08) | Inherited | Provided by GitHub Pages / hosting platform HTTPS, not an app-level control |
| Encryption at rest (03.13.16) | N/A for app storage | No server-side data at rest. Optional client-side AES-256-GCM for exported profile JSON |
| Audit log retention and tamper resistance | N/A | No server-side logs. Calculation history is browser-local and operator-controlled |

