*T/O Structure Fields:* `Unit`, `UnitName`, `BMOS`, `PayGrade`, `Authorized`, `BilletDescription` — **No CUI, No PII.** All are organizational T/O data.

*Critical MOS Fields:* `MOS`, `Description`, `Category`, `UnitType` — **No CUI, No PII.** Reference data only.

**PoC DETERMINATION:** With synthetic data (EDIPIs prefixed `99`, placeholder names), **zero fields contain real CUI or real PII**. The PoC Hard Limit (Step 3) is satisfied. If an operator loads real alpha roster data, fields `EDIPI`, `LastName`, `FirstName`, `MI`, `Sex`, `EAS`, and `EDD` become Non-Sensitive PII (linkable in combination), and `EDIPI` becomes Sensitive PII. At that point the system would cross the PoC boundary and require the controls documented in Parts 4-7.

