## PART 7: AUTHORIZATION PATHWAY (MANDATORY BEFORE ANY DEPLOYMENT)

### Authority: DoDI 8500.01; DoDI 8510.01; DD Form 2875

The following authorizations must be obtained IN WRITING before the system moves from PoC to any form of real-user access.

Authorization Item 1 - Chain of Command Written Authorization:
Verbal approval, informal feedback, and supervisory awareness do not constitute authorization. The chain of command must provide written, signed authorization for the specific function of the application. Document the date, name, and position of the authorizing official.

Authorization Item 2 - Privacy Act Coordinator (PAC) Review:
If any PII is involved, the PAC must review and provide written authorization per DoDI 5400.11. Verbal clearance is not authorization.

Authorization Item 3 - Information Assurance Officer (IAO) / ISSO Review:
If the system connects to any DoD network or processes data from a DoD IS, the IAO or ISSO must review and provide written sign-off.

Authorization Item 4 - ATO (if DoD IS):
If the system meets the DoDI 8500.01 definition of a DoD Information System, no operational use occurs without an ATO from the Authorizing Official.

Authorization Item 5 - DD Form 2875 (SAAR) Currency Check:
Confirm the current edition (2020 revision) is on file. Reject and replace any 2009 or earlier edition forms. Document the date the form was updated.

**THE DOCUMENTATION PRINCIPLE:**
Informal praise, positive reviews, and absence of objection do not equal authorization. Written authorization from a named, positioned official with the authority to grant it is the only form that provides legal protection.

